 them low health, or they will magically warp back to their bind points and regenerate.  I liked this camp, it was steady xp, rarely camped as most people don't kill dorfs, dorf heads sold for good cash, and there is a nice fast repop, so when you are fm again, they are either up or spawn right after you walk down to them. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.sillyjanine.com/mybases.html"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.cestusdei.org/uploads/images/luxysig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oaklenia>Oaklenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/03 8:48:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26190.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding Expo Guards in GD</span><hr size=1> First I'd like to say that while on the surface it may not appear that these are the most stellar XP, you must consider the danger/adds(time sucks) threat involved. Yes, I have quadded flies in PoD, yes I have quadded ravens in PoN, but at level 58 where I am, this is simply the best place to be while you are LF a group when you consider how SAFE it is. PoD flies are easy on their own, but managing adds is tricky and often deadly. Ravens in PoN are free of adds but take a lot of mana and is very hard to finish (at least for me) without harvesting (in which case you will have to be too far away and they will regen). These guys are roughly 1.25% XP at 58, bout 4% AAXP, but it really adds up after a bit when you realize that you have not died cuz of stupid PoP mobs trashing the piss outta joo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I have died once since starting these at dinging level 57 to 40% through 58. (stupid warping bug)<br>
<br>
As for the guide:<br>
1.) invis up<br>
2.) head past the first circular room, then take your left fork, then your right. You should be at the entrance to a room with 2 ex. gaurds near the door. <br>
3.) As said above, RS3 is plenty. Now get a running start so they dont bash ya (have one targeted) and TFlux. Both will aggro.<br>
4.) KEEP THEM CLOSE TO YOU. If you run too far ahead cuz you're afraid of them wailin on you, you WILL lose them and either wind up kiting only 2, or dead when they warp<br>
5.) Now with them CLOSE behind, run toward the entrance until you are just far enough from the front two gaurds so that they will not aggro. Stand there and wait until the first 2 (already aggroed) are RIGHT on your tail. As you just escape from them, target one of the two at the entrance and flux as you run out of the tunnel. &lt;--- prob. not actually necessary as the first 2 will aggro the 2nd pair, but I just like to make sure.<br>
6.) Now continue to keep them CLOSE behind as you head out of the tunnel. Once you are out, it's gravy. Round up. Snare. Quad. OH BTW - No you do not need to snare twice, it is a waste of mana. I have never snared this quad more than once, ever. (discounting the occasional resist on the original snare)<br>
7.) Takes about 85-90% of my mana w/ KEI at level 58. The repop time is perfect with just KEI on, they repop as you are hitting 80/85 mana-ish, take them then and by the time they are out of the tunnel, snared, and ready to go you will be 90/95 and g2g.<br>
<br>
Did I mention keep them close to you while you are bringing them out of the tunnel? Unless you like &quot;quadding&quot; only two dwarves, or are fond of having all four warp on top and kill you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=630472" target="top">Oaklenia Somesweetlastname</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Burning things to a crisp for 58 levels<br>
